msContents.summary: Collection of medical preparations for a wide variety of ailments, including headaches, eye problems, toothaches, animal bites, gout, and pleurisy, with more general introductory material on the four elements, the four humors, the signs of the zodiac, and the planets.
msContents.textLang: Middle French, with some sections in Latin (f. 77r-81v, 85v-87r, 93r-98r, 137v, 141r)

supportDesc.extent: 147 leaves : 200 x 144 (138 x 85) mm. bound to 208 x 150 mm

collation.p: Paper, 147; 1-2¹² 3¹⁰ 4-7¹² 8¹²(-1) 9¹²(-1) 10¹⁴(-1) 11-12¹² ii 13⁴; [1-147], modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto (f. 12-55 with early foliation in roman numerals, 1-44). Catchwords on gatherings 4-7 and 9-12, last verso, lower center or lower right (f. 46v, 58v, 70v, 82v, 104v, 117, 129v, 141v). References in this record are to modern foliation.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 22-26 long lines; mostly frame-ruled in faint ink, some with double horizontal bounding lines. Pricking visible on one leaf (f. 24).

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in Gothic cursive script by multiple hands.

binding.p: Original (late 15th-century) boards with remnants of original calf binding; remnant of a boss, central lower cover; spine and clasp lacking.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by John D. Stanitz (Cleveland, Ohio), Ms. 51.
Acquired by Lawrence J. Schoenberg with other Stanitz manuscripts, Sept. 1997.
